{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, rendered documentation webpages produced by DocC come with a default"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"visual styling. If you wish, you may make adjustments to this styling by adding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an optional "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":" file to the root of your documentation catalog"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with some configuration. This file is used to customize various things like"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"colors and fonts. You can even make changes to the way that specific elements"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appear, like buttons, code listings, and asides. Additionally, some metadata for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the website can be configured in this file, and it can also be used to opt in or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"opt out of certain default rendering behavior."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you’re curious about the full capabilities of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":" file,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can check out the latest Open API specification for it "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-docc\/blob\/main\/Sources\/SwiftDocC\/SwiftDocC.docc\/Resources\/ThemeSettings.spec.json"},{"type":"text","text":", which"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"documents all valid settings that could be present."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s walk through some basic examples of customizing the appearance of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"documentation now."}]},{"anchor":"Colors","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Colors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"DocC utilizes "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/drafts.csswg.org\/css-variables\/"},{"type":"text","text":" (CSS variables) to define the various"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"colors that are used throughout the HTML elements of rendered documentation. Any"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"key\/value in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme.color"},{"type":"text","text":" object of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":" will either"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"update an existing color property used in the renderer or add a new one that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"could be referenced by existing ones."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As a simple example, the following configuration would update the background"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"fill color for the “documentation intro” element to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"rebeccapurple\""},{"type":"text","text":" by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"changing the value of the CSS property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"--color-documentation-intro-fill: \"rebeccapurple\""},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","  \"theme\": {","    \"color\": {","      \"documentation-intro-fill\": \"rebeccapurple\"","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-01.png"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that any valid CSS color value could be used. Here is a more advanced"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example which demonstrates how specialized dark and light versions of the main"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"background fill and nav colors could be defined as varying lightness percentages"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a green hue."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","  \"theme\": {","    \"color\": {","      \"hue-green\": \"120\",","      \"fill\": {","        \"dark\": \"hsl(var(--color-hue-green), 100%, 10%)\",","        \"light\": \"hsl(var(--color-hue-green), 100%, 90%)\"","      },","      \"fill-secondary\": {","        \"dark\": \"hsl(var(--color-hue-green), 100%, 20%)\",","        \"light\": \"hsl(var(--color-hue-green), 100%, 80%)\"","      },","      \"nav-solid-background\": \"var(--color-fill)\"","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-02.png"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-03.png"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As a general rule, the default color properties provided by DocC assumes a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"naming convention where “fill” colors are used for backgrounds and “figure”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"colors are used for foreground colors, like text."}]},{"style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a more complete example of a fully customized documentation website, you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can check out "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/mportiz08.github.io\/swift-docc\/documentation\/docc"},{"type":"text","text":" of the DocC documentation that is using this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/mportiz08.github.io\/swift-docc\/theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Tip"},{"anchor":"Fonts","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Fonts"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By default, there are two main fonts used by DocC: one for monospaced text in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"code voice and another for all other text content. With "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you can customize the CSS "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"font-family"},{"type":"text","text":" lists for these however you choose."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","  \"theme\": {","    \"typography\": {","      \"html-font\": \"\\\"Comic Sans MS\\\", \\\"Comic Sans\\\", cursive\",","      \"html-font-mono\": \"\\\"Courier New\\\", Courier, monospace\"","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-04"}]},{"anchor":"Borders","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Borders"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Another aspect of the renderer that you may wish to modify is the way that it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"applies border to certain elements. With "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":", you can change"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the default border radius for all elements and also individually update the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"border styles for asides, buttons, code listings, and tutorial steps."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","  \"theme\": {","    \"aside\": {","      \"border-radius\": \"6px\",","      \"border-style\": \"double\",","      \"border-width\": \"3px\"","    },","    \"border-radius\": \"0\",","    \"button\": {","      \"border-radius\": \"8px\",","      \"border-style\": \"solid\",","      \"border-width\": \"2px\"","    },","    \"code\": {","      \"border-radius\": \"2px\",","      \"border-style\": \"dashed\",","      \"border-width\": \"2px\"","    },","    \"tutorial-step\": {","      \"border-radius\": \"12px\"","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-05.png"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-06.png"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-07.png"}]},{"anchor":"Icons","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Icons"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is also possible to use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":" to specify custom icons to use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in place of the default ones provided by DocC. There are a few basic steps to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"follow in order to override an icon:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Find the identifier that maps to the icon you want to override."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add this value as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":" attribute to the new SVG icon."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Associate a relative or absolute URL to the new SVG icon with the identifier"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"You can find all the possible identifier values for every valid icon kind in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the Open API "},{"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"specification"}],"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-docc\/blob\/main\/Sources\/SwiftDocC\/SwiftDocC.docc\/Resources\/ThemeSettings.spec.json","overridingTitle":"specification"},{"type":"text","text":" for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As a simple example, here is how you could update the icon used for articles in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the sidebar to be a simple box:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Find the identifier for article icons: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"article\""}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Add the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id=\"article\""},{"type":"text","text":" attribute to the new SVG icon: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"simple-box.svg"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"svg","code":["<svg viewBox=\"0 0 14 14\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" id=\"article\">","  <rect x=\"2\" y=\"2\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\" stroke=\"currentColor\" fill=\"none\"><\/rect>","<\/svg>"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configure "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":" to map the URL for the new article icon"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","  \"theme\": {","    \"icons\": {","      \"article\": \"\/images\/simple-box.svg\"","    }","  }","}"]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-08.png"}]},{"anchor":"Metadata","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Metadata"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can specify some text that will be used in the HTML "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"<title>"},{"type":"text","text":" element for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all webpages in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":" in place of the default “Documentation”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"text."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","  \"meta\": {","    \"title\": \"Custom Title\",","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With that configuration, the title of this page would change from “Customizing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Your Documentation Appearance | Documentation” to “Customizing Your Documentation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Appearance | "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom Title"}]},{"type":"text","text":"”."}]},{"anchor":"Feature-Flags","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Feature Flags"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"From time to time, there may be instances of various experimental UI features"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that can be enabled or disabled using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"theme-settings.json"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Example"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As of the time of writing this, there is only one available “quick navigation”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"feature that is disabled by default and can be enabled with the following"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configuration. Note that this flag may be dropped in the future and new ones may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be added as necessary for other features."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"json","code":["{","  \"features\": {","    \"docs\": {","      \"quickNavigation\": {","        \"enable\": true","      }","    }","  }","}"]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/docc\/customizing-the-appearance-of-your-documentation-pages"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/DocC\/customizing-the-appearance-of-your-documentation-pages","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Customize the look and feel of your documentation webpages."}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Customizing the Appearance of Your Documentation Pages","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"DocC"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/DocC"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Distribution","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/DocC\/distributing-documentation-to-other-developers"],"generated":true}],"references":{"theme-screenshot-07.png":{"alt":"A screenshot of a documentation page with custom code listing and aside border","type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-07.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-07.png","traits":["1x","light"]},{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-07~dark.png","traits":["1x","dark"]}]},"theme-screenshot-02.png":{"alt":"A screenshot of the green page background in dark mode","type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-02.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-02.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"theme-screenshot-01.png":{"alt":"A screenshot of the documentation intro element with a purple background color","type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-01.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-01.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"theme-screenshot-06.png":{"alt":"A screenshot of tutorial steps with custom borders","type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-06.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-06.png","traits":["1x","light"]},{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-06~dark.png","traits":["1x","dark"]}]},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/DocC":{"role":"collection","title":"DocC","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Produce rich API reference documentation and interactive tutorials for your Swift framework or package."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/DocC","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/docc"},"https://drafts.csswg.org/css-variables/":{"title":"CSS custom properties","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CSS custom properties"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/drafts.csswg.org\/css-variables\/","url":"https:\/\/drafts.csswg.org\/css-variables\/"},"https://mportiz08.github.io/swift-docc/theme-settings.json":{"title":"theme-settings.json file","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"theme-settings.json file"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/mportiz08.github.io\/swift-docc\/theme-settings.json","url":"https:\/\/mportiz08.github.io\/swift-docc\/theme-settings.json"},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/DocC/distributing-documentation-to-other-developers":{"role":"article","title":"Distributing Documentation to Other Developers","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Share your documentation by hosting it on a web server."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/DocC\/distributing-documentation-to-other-developers","kind":"article","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/docc\/distributing-documentation-to-other-developers"},"theme-screenshot-04":{"alt":"A screenshot of a documentation page with custom fonts","type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-04","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-04.png","traits":["1x","light"]},{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-04~dark.png","traits":["1x","dark"]}]},"theme-screenshot-03.png":{"alt":"A screenshot of the green page background in light mode","type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-03.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-03.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"theme-screenshot-08.png":{"alt":"A screenshot of the sidebar using a custom icon for","type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-08.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-08@2x.png","traits":["2x","light"]},{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-08~dark@2x.png","traits":["2x","dark"]}]},"https://github.com/apple/swift-docc/blob/main/Sources/SwiftDocC/SwiftDocC.docc/Resources/ThemeSettings.spec.json":{"title":"here","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"here"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-docc\/blob\/main\/Sources\/SwiftDocC\/SwiftDocC.docc\/Resources\/ThemeSettings.spec.json","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-docc\/blob\/main\/Sources\/SwiftDocC\/SwiftDocC.docc\/Resources\/ThemeSettings.spec.json"},"theme-screenshot-05.png":{"alt":"A screenshot of a tutorial page with custom button","type":"image","identifier":"theme-screenshot-05.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/theme-screenshot-05.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://mportiz08.github.io/swift-docc/documentation/docc":{"title":"this fork","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"this fork"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/mportiz08.github.io\/swift-docc\/documentation\/docc","url":"https:\/\/mportiz08.github.io\/swift-docc\/documentation\/docc"}}}